    {
      "id": "9a0bf30f_e5567917",
      "file_path": "jtosca/src/main/java/org/onap/sdc/toscaparser/api/NodeTemplate.java",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 95,
      "message": "ArtifactTypeDef represents a tosca artifact type definition (tosca simple yaml profile 1.3 ch 3.7.4), i.e. definition of a type of artifact, an example of which is the definition of tosca.artifacts.asd.deploymentItem\n\nWhat we have on a node template are artifact definitions (ch 3.6.7), i.e. a definition of a file. The file is associated with a tosac artifact type but they are seperate concepts. \n\nSo the ArtifactTypeDef is not a correct class to use here (for example the getParentType method reads the \"derived_from\" in the definition - this is fine for an artifact type definition but not for an artifact definition)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
      },
      "updated": "2022-04-19 13:22:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
